This course has six three-hour sessions, each session has 1.5 h lecture and 1.5 h seminar with active contribution from participants.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to give an overview of new drug classes used in oncology, drug development and clinical trials in oncology and principles of systemic treatment of common solid tumours.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1. Better understanding of drugs used in oncology 2. Give an overview of systemic treatment in various malignant tumours and treatment related side effects 3. Increase an interest in drug development and clinical trials in oncology
